DOM (DOCUMENT OBJECT MODEL)
	It  is used in web development used to interact and manipulate(change)the html documents
	When the webpage loaded, the browser created dom of the web page 
	When the html file is loaded into browser
	The java script cannot understand the html document directly 
DOM : IT IS basically the representation of the same html document but in a tree-like structure composed of object
Keypoints  :
1)structure : the dom represents the structure of html document as a tree each node in tree represents   the elements , an attributes or text
2)manipulation: using   java script   you can interact with elements ( 5buttons , paragraphs)on the webpage , changing the content  ,styles ,can add or remove elements
3) event handling you can handle the interacts like click or pressing the button
4)W3C world wide web consortium  
METHOD of 
Getting an element by id
Getting an element by class
Getting an element by tag
Getting an element by query
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <style>
        .a{
            color: blue;
        }
        .b{
            color: aqua;
        }
        .c{
            color: red;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1 class="a">saicharan</h1>
    <h1 class="b">sainath</h1>
    <h1 class="c">Ramya</h1>
    <h1 class="a">Rahul</h1>
    <h1 class="c">kavya</h1>
</body>
</html>-

